<p>I created a class, and I need it to access a repository object which is autowired in myController class. Is there a way to do that? Or should I create new Repository for my new class (but I doubt that it would be a good idea since this new class operates on the same database).</p>  <pre><code>@RestController @RequestMapping("/sth") final class myController {      @Autowired     MyRepository repository;      //here goes the rest of the code }   @Repository final public class MyRepository {      @Autowired     protected JdbcTemplate jdbc;      //the rest of the code }  class Another {      //here I want to write something to the repository object! }  @Configuration class AuditEventLogConfiguration implements ApplicationListener&lt;AbstractAuthenticationEvent&gt; {      @Override     public void onApplicationEvent(AbstractAuthenticationEvent event) {         //here I create "Another" object     } } </code></pre>